 <text>
  <front>
   <head>To a Lady, who valu'd herself on speaking her Mind in a blunt Manner, which she call'd being sincere.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">you  display,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">A Virtue wond'rous rare!</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Nor value, tho' the World should say,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">You're , so you're</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To be , then, give  leave;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And I will frankly own,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Since you but this  Virtue have,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">'Twere better you had</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
